text: [S1] Did you see that documentary about octopuses last night?
[S2] No, I missed it. Was it good?
[S1] Incredible! They showed one using coconut shells as armor. It carried them around and hid inside when threatened.
[S2] That's amazing. I had no idea they were that smart.
[S1] They can solve puzzles, open jars from the inside, and even recognize individual humans. Some aquariums have to octopus-proof their tanks because they're escape artists.
[S2] Wait, they can recognize people? How do they even test that?
[S1] The researchers wore different colored shirts and one would feed them while another would poke them with a stick. The octopuses would hide from the poker but come out for the feeder.
[S2] That's both fascinating and slightly terrifying. Eight arms and a grudge.
